==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Odontoblast
<hw>O*don"to*blast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Odonto-</ets> + <ets>-blast</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of the more or less columnar
cells on the outer surface of the pulp of a tooth; an odontoplast. They
are supposed to be connected with the formation of dentine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the cells which secrete
the chitinous teeth of Mollusca.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 997 --></p>

<p><ent>Odontocete</ent>⟦br⟧
